
4 slices bacon, chopped
2 Tbsp butter
1 cup diced onion
3/4 cup diced celery
1/2 cup diced carrot
13-18 oz clams
2.5-3 cups clam juice or chicken broth
3 cups diced potatoes
1 Tbsp sherry or lemon juice
1 tsp salt
1 tsp pepper
2 tsp chopped thyme
1 bay leaf
1 cup heavy cream
1.5 Tbsp cornstarch
2 Tbsp water
1 can corn

Instant Pot: saute bacon until it just starts to crisp then remove all but 1 Tbsp of fat.

Add butter, onions, celery, and carrot.
Saute 2 or 3 minutes.
Stir in the garlic and press cancel.

Drain the clams and add juice (or chicken broth) to get 3.5 cups.
Add the juice to the pot (clams remain out for now).
Deglaze the pot.
Add potatoes, sherry (or lemon juice), salt, pepper, thyme, and bay leaf.

Close pot and set valve to sealing.  Press pressure cook and set time to 5 minutes.
Let release for 2 minutes, then remove lid.

Use potato masher to break up potatoes.  Press Saute and
add clams and cream.

If you want it thicker, mix cornstarch and water and stir in, stirring
constantly.  Bring to a boil.
